author: Yizhou Shan
message:
[Stack backtrace is working, thanks to stack unwinder]

Print backtrace is actually very simple: you go through the stack
and find the possible kernel addresses. With the FRAME_POINTER option,
the unwinder can tell which is in the real call trace and which are just
stale values in the stack (with a prefix '?').

Without FRAME_POINTER, a lot of information will be missing. So despite
push %rbp and pop %rbp brings more instructions, the much more friendly
debug info with FRAME_POINTER on can make our debugging life easier.
files_changed: arch/x86/include/asm/page_types.h, arch/x86/include/asm/stacktrace.h, arch/x86/include/asm/unwind.h, arch/x86/kernel/dumpstack.c, arch/x86/kernel/unwind_frame.c, arch/x86/kernel/unwind_guess.c, init/Kconfig

author: Yizhou Shan
message:
Add CONFIG_TRAMPOLINE_START, make the address fixed

We used to use the setup image's base address, which is passed
by bootparam. This will have a problem is the reported address
is not aligned to PAGE_SIZE.

If it is not aligned to PAGE_SIZE, then the smpboot code will
fail to boot the secondary cpus because of the realmode segment
thing I think.

Anyway, to make life easier and easy-to-debug, just make it fixed.
Default to 0x90000 now.

Signed-off-by: Yizhou Shan <shan13@purdue.edu>

author: Yizhou Shan
message:
[Patch] alloc_page: build zonelist based on real node order

Fixed several TODOs in page allocation. alloc_page_nodemask
will take a zonelist, and walk through it until it find a page
to allocate. Normally, the first zone will satisfy the allocation.

Each node has its own zonelist. The order of zones within zonelist
become *very* important. Because it determines where the page will be
allocated from.

Previously, the initilization of zonelist is simplified, so every node's
zonelist are the same: node 0's zone comes first.

In this patch, I changed the initilization. The zonelist is built in the
way that the numa_distance is taken into consideration. And each node
will finally has its own zone comes first at its own zonelist.

Anyway, this is the right way, and correct semantic alloc_page_nodemask
should provide.

Besides, alloc_pages() will use smp_node_id() instead of NUMA_NO_NODE.

smp_node_id() is lego specific.

Signed-off-by: Yizhou Shan <shan13@purdue.edu>
files_changed: Documentation/parameters.txt, arch/x86/include/asm/numa.h, arch/x86/include/asm/smp.h, arch/x86/kernel/percpu.c, arch/x86/mm/numa.c, include/lego/mm.h, include/lego/workqueue.h, kernel/workqueue.c, mm/page_alloc.c

author: Yizhou Shan
message:
bug fix: initiliaze the variable if NUMA_USE_ONE_SOCKET is off

NUMA_USE_ONE_SOCKET normally is off for memory manager. When
this is the case, we should always boot all sockets if NUMA is on.

Initialize the boot_this_node variable!

author: yilun
message:
Processor: add dummy socket/connect

If SOCKET_SYSCALL is not configured in Processor, we create a dummy socket file
operations. Because TensorFlow will try to create a socket, and try to connect,
If TF failed to connect, it will close the socket.

So, if socket does not present, it does not hurt. We just need to provide a dummy
implementation.

But remove this once socket is all tested, and built-in by default.
